<b>Observation of regular polygons</b>
July 5th 2022

For any regular polygons of side length n, it's area is equal to n^2 times the area of the regular polygon of side length 1.

<img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/TealEgg/MoosaNasir/main/AreaPolygon.png" alt="Area Polygon">

This can be best shown is the tiling polygons, but works with any other polygon as well (ex. pentagon, heptagon, octagon, etc.)
